\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 A similar display of harmony and solidarity can be observed in hives. The devotion of worker bees is especially reminiscent of ants.}{\f0\fs22\insrsid10365038 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  }{
\f0\fs22\insrsid9665616\charrsid10365038 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Bot\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 h species work tirelessly until they die\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 for the sake of the queen and for the larvae which are not theirs.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 A beehive's population consists of the queen, the drone males responsible for fertilizing the queen and the hundreds if not thousands of worker bees\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
. All work is performed by the workers: building the combs, cleaning and defending the hive, feeding the queen and the drones, caring for the larvae, building and preparing the brooding chambers according to the type of bee (worker, queen, drone) that wil
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 develop inside, cleaning the hive and regulating its humidity and temperature, feeding the larvae according their specific needs (nectar, honey and pollen), and collecting nectar, pollen, water and resins.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 We can list the phases of a worker bee's life and\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  its devotional behavior as follows:
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 1. A worker's lifespan is between four and six weeks. Once it emerges from the pupal stage, it works for approximately three }{\f0\fs22\expnd-1\expndtw-5\insrsid9665616\charrsid10365038 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
weeks inside the hive. Its first job is to nurse the developing larvae. The worker lives off t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
he pollen and honey from the feed store, but feeds most of it to the larvae. It regurgitates some of the food it has eaten, mixes it with substances drawn from glands inside its head, and feeds this mixture to the larvae.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 How does a creature which has just\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 emerged from the pupa know its job? Why do all bees comply without objection? The bee ought to emerge from the pupa and seek to continue its own life without showing any signs of conscious devotion. But not so: The bee fulfills its nursing duties in a hi
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 g\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 hly disciplined, responsible manner.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 2. When the bee is approximately twelve days old, its wax glands develop and it begins to restore and build the hexagonal comb structures in which larvae develop and honey is stored.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
3. Between the age of twelve days and three weeks, the worker receives the pollen and nectar brought back to the hive by the other bees, converts it into honey and stores it. It also cleans the hive, removing from it dead bees and other waste.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 4. When it h\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
as reached the age of three weeks, it's old enough to gather the nectar, pollen, water and resins needed in the hive. These mature workers leave the hive to look for flowers and nectar. Obtaining food is a tiring process: After only two to three weeks, a 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 w\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 orker bee will die of exhaustion.}{\f0\fs22\insrsid9665616\charrsid10365038 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 139}{\f0\fs22\expnd-1\expndtw-5\insrsid9665616\charrsid10365038 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 However, a point hard to explain is that each bee produces far more honey than it requires for its own needs. It is impossible for evolutionists to explain why \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
an unthinking creature, supposedly in a struggle for its own survival, should persist in this hard work without ever giving up.
